Different Priors

Distribution of errors of factor loadings across three priors:

  • Population mean of factor loading : 1.156 from logn(0.1, 0.3)

  • Uniform (0, 10) : mean = 5; (The prior mean is over)

  • Std Normal (0, 1) : mean = 0.399; (The prior mean is under)

  • lognoraml (0, 5) : mean = 2.6833729^{5} (with restriction at 20, 1.995); (The prior mean is over)
